field.value:
Permissions

Permissions in the system are managed based on roles that exist. The current roles in the system are Consumer, Contributor, Collaborator and Manager. There is another role that exists - "Administrator", but the role of the administrator is given only to some users that will have full permissions on the system and it is not part of the current functionality.
Each Object in the system could have special permissions that cover the security policy in the organization.

The permissions can be inherit:

  • library level
  • parent lelel
  • special permissions to be set upped

In general, for each user/ group could be given one of the following roles:

  • Consumer could only view the object (project, case, document, cultural object), cannot edit it or edit uploaded content
  • Contributor could create new objects and edit only the objects he/ she created
  • Collaborator could create new objects and edit the objects he/ she created and objects created by others
  • Manager has full permissions on the object could edit/ delete objects created by himself and by other users, could manage the permissions on the object
